<content>This sample is for converting image syntax.

Xwiki example:
{image:img.png}
{image:img.png|30}
{image:img.png| |20}
{image:img.png|30|20}

All params, based on doc found here:
http://code.xwiki.org/xwiki/bin/view/Macros/ImageMacro

alt: {image:cow.jpg|alt=A Cow. Moo}
width/height: {image:gamesigns.jpg|height=128|width=128}
align: {image:cow.jpg|align=right}
halign: {image:cow.jpg|halign=floatleft}
document: {image:img.png|document=XWiki.XWikiSyntax}
link: {image:img.jpg|link=}
fromIncludingDoc: {image:img.png|fromIncludingDoc=}

What happens when the image is right next to something else
Text{image:cow.jpg}Something else

What about an attachment link (instead of inline)
{attach:wiki.png}
